<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900430-0006</DOCNO><DOCID>900430-0006.</DOCID><HL>   Who's News:   Herman Miller's Ruch   Adds President's Post</HL><DATE>04/30/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   MLHR WNEWS</CO><LP>   ZEELAND, Mich. -- Herman Miller Inc., an office furnituremaker, said Richard H. Ruch, 60-year-old chief executiveofficer, was elected to the additional post of president,succeeding Edward R. Simon, 52.   Mr. Simon said earlier this month that he was resigning to&quot;provide {Mr. Ruch} with an opportunity for further alignmentof the organization.&quot;</LP><TEXT>   Philip J. Mercorella, 45, president of the Milcare Inc.unit, was named senior vice president, global sales,marketing and dealer distribution, succeeding DavidArmstrong, 54, who is taking early retirement as senior vicepresident, sales and marketing. The company said Mr.Mercorella's post involves broader responsibilities than Mr.Armstrong had. Mr. Mercorella will remain Milcare presidentuntil a successor is named.</TEXT></DOC>